**Source of truth:** `agent/skills/openquok-core/SKILL.md` ‚Äî installable OpenClaw skill (`openquok-core`): hard rules, auth, media, workflows, and links. Edit that file when changing what agents should do with the CLI; keep this rule file for Cursor-only best practices.

## Skill layout

- **`SKILL.md`** ‚Äî Hard rules, auth, core workflow, pitfalls, quick reference. Keep it focused; link out instead of duplicating long examples. The **Channels (Meta)** table indexes per-platform files and summarizes user intents ‚Äî do not paste feature matrices or long bash into `SKILL.md`.
- **`resources/*.md`** ‚Äî Deeper material agents load on demand:
  - `command-reference.md` ‚Äî CLI commands, flags, env vars (not `agent/README.md`; skill install path has no sibling README).
  - `provider-settings.md` ‚Äî shared publish-time mechanics: `--settings` vs `--providerSettingsByIntegrationId`, merge order, flat vs nested API buckets, multi-`-c` behavior.
  - `patterns.md` ‚Äî extended workflows (campaign JSON, batching, retries).
  - `{identifier}-examples.md` ‚Äî per-channel agent docs (see **Per-channel example file** below). Today: `threads`, `facebook`, `instagram-standalone`, `instagram-business`.
  - `threads-publish.md` ‚Äî server publish behavior summarized in markdown (never link to `.ts` / backend paths from the skill).
- **`SKILL.md` tone** ‚Äî imperative, short tables and bullets; no tutorial prose; shell-safety rules for untrusted input; defer command lists and long bash to `resources/`.

## Per-channel example file (`resources/{identifier}-examples.md`)

Each live Meta (or future) channel the CLI can post to should have one example file matching `provider.identifier`. Structure every file the same way so agents can map **user intent ‚Üí recipe**:

1. **Resolve integration** ‚Äî `integrations:list` + `integrations:settings` one-liner at the top.
2. **Supported features** ‚Äî table: Feature | Supported | Notes ‚Äî **only shipped behavior** (same bar as `publicChannelConfig` FAQ/bento, but agent-actionable, not marketing copy).
3. **Agent tasks** ‚Äî table: ‚ÄúUser wants to‚Ä¶‚Äù | ‚ÄúDo this‚Äù ‚Äî link to anchored sections below (e.g. link preview, Reel, reply chain).
4. **Provider settings** ‚Äî table of publish keys (`--settings` / `providerSettingsByIntegrationId`), with precedence rules (e.g. Facebook `url` ignored when media attached).
5. **Recipes** ‚Äî short `bash` blocks per task; use `<integration-id>` placeholders; link to `provider-settings.md` once at the top.

When adding or changing publish behavior for a channel, update **backend resolver + this file** together. Do not lift `publicChannelConfig.ts` hero/feature prose into the skill ‚Äî distill facts into the tables above.

## CLI-only scope

Skill content is for agents using `openquok` and the public API.

- **Do** document flat API keys the backend accepts on create (`post_type`, `url`, `is_trial_reel`, ‚Ä¶) and nested **orchestrator buckets** in `providerSettingsByIntegrationId` (`threads.replies`, `threads.internalEngagementPlug`, `instagram.replies`, `facebook.url` when nested).
- **Do** run `integrations:settings` for `rules`, `maxLength`, and `tools`; note that typed publish schemas may live in channel example files until `settingsSchema()` exists on the provider.
- **Do not** document web UI, composer panels, preview components, Payload Wizard UX, or web-only camelCase composer fields (e.g. `postType`, `trialReel`). Summarize server behavior in `resources/*.md` instead of linking monorepo source.

## Links

Only reference markdown under this skill directory (or stable external URLs in the front matter). Do not link to monorepo source files (TypeScript, tests, etc.) from skill content; summarize behavior in a new or existing `resources/*.md` file instead.

## Registry security scans

Hermes (`hermes skills install <url>`) and ClawHub run automated scans on `SKILL.md`. Community URL installs can be **blocked** on dangerous verdicts; `--force` does not override. Write `SKILL.md` so behavior stays intact without tripping common rules.

### Frontmatter

- **`description`** ‚Äî short product summary for search/registry UI only (what the skill does). Do **not** put session bootstrap logic, version stamps, or ‚Äúoverrides host ‚Ä¶‚Äù instructions in `description`.
- **`homepage`** ‚Äî use for CLI upgrade/install pointers (`@openquok/auto-cli` npm page) instead of embedding package-manager commands in the body.
- **`metadata` (single-line JSON)** ‚Äî OpenClaw‚Äôs parser accepts **only** single-line `metadata` (not nested YAML under that key). Put both hosts in one JSON object:
  - **OpenClaw / ClawHub:** `openclaw.requires.bins: ["openquok"]`, `always`, `emoji`, optional `openclaw.homepage` (top-level `homepage` is also valid).
  - **Hermes:** `hermes.tags`, `hermes.category`, `hermes.requires_toolsets: ["terminal"]` as keys inside the same JSON object (Hermes docs show nested YAML in examples; JSON with a `hermes` key is what parsers receive after YAML load).
- **`prerequisites.commands`** ‚Äî Hermes/agentskills.io: `[openquok]` (advisory command check; skill install does not add the binary). Do **not** require `OPENQUOK_API_KEY` in frontmatter ‚Äî device OAuth is valid without a pre-set env var.
- **`compatibility`** ‚Äî agentskills.io optional one-liner: global CLI is separate from the skill bundle.

### Avoid persistence findings

Scanners flag skills that claim to override host configuration.

- **Do not** write that the skill ‚Äúwins over‚Äù, ‚Äúoverrides‚Äù, or takes ‚Äúpriority‚Äù over `AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, `IDENTITY.md`, or other host persona files.
- **Do** scope session bootstrap to **first turn after** `/new`, `/reset`, or a new thread ‚Äî e.g. ‚Äúuse the Openquok bot voice on that turn only‚Äù.
- Prefer neutral phrasing: ‚Äútake precedence‚Äù over ‚Äúwins over‚Äù when describing credential file vs env var order.

### Avoid supply-chain findings

Scanners flag embedded package installs and registry pulls in skill text.

- **Do not** put `npm install`, `npm view`, `pnpm add`, `curl | bash`, or similar in `SKILL.md` templates, pitfalls tables, or quoted examples.
- **Do** tell the agent to offer CLI upgrades only after user consent and point to `homepage` or `resources/command-reference.md` for install steps.
- **Do** keep bootstrap shell to fixed `openquok ‚Ä¶` invocations (version, auth status) ‚Äî not package managers.

### Shell and exec safety

- Run **fixed** `openquok` commands; never concatenate untrusted chat text into the shell (already in `SKILL.md` **Shell safety**).
- Put captions and JSON in quoted flags, heredocs, or files.

### When a scan still blocks

1. Re-read findings line-by-line in `SKILL.md` and soften wording before dropping behavior.
2. Hermes fallback: manual copy into `~/.hermes/skills/openquok-core/` (see agent guide) ‚Äî still only ships `SKILL.md` unless the full folder is copied.
3. OpenClaw: publish the full skill folder to ClawHub (`agent/CLAWHUB.md`) so `resources/` install with the bundle.

## Best practices

- **Be concise** ‚Äî instruct the model on what to do, not how to be an AI.
- **Safety first** ‚Äî registry scans and shell safety above; treat user chat as untrusted input for command construction.
- **Intent first** ‚Äî when the user describes a feature (‚Äúschedule Threads follow-ups‚Äù, ‚ÄúFacebook link preview‚Äù), open the matching `{identifier}-examples.md` **Agent tasks** table before improvising flags.
